HEADWORD: Genoese
<hw>Gen`o*ese"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Genoa, a city of Italy; <as>as, the <ex>Genoese</ex> sailor we call
Columbus</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Genoa; collectively, the people of Genoa.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Genovese.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

